          "date": "2016-09-29 20:08:23.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-8264 tests: setstripe striping parameters not inherited",
        "message": "LU-8264 tests: setstripe striping parameters not inherited\n\nWhen a user specifies any striping parameters in ‘lfs setstripe’, all\nstriping parameters come from the client and are not inherited from\nthe parent directory. There are several tests in the ost-pools script\nthat should detected this lack of inheritance from the parent\ndirectory.\n\nIn ost-pools.sh, modify\n\n1. test 6 to check the directory and file created by calling\n‘lfs setstripe –c -1’ with no pool specified. Also, modify the pool\nto contain only half the available OSTs so that using ‘-c -1’ with set\nstripe is easily able to be checked.\n2. test 20 to check that files and directories inherit the correct\npool information and that striping parameters to ‘lfs setstripe’ does\nnot alter this inheritance.\n\nSome other minor clean up to the ost-pools script like removing\nunnecessary calls to return after a call to ‘error’ and add a\nmore detail to an error message.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I316c094b03ef03965f1d3ba1510f51c26350dc4f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
